denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Beville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Middlesex and Surrey; of Norman origin): variant of   Bovill  . Derivation from Beuville (Calvados) is also possible, though unproven.","French (also <b>Béville</b>): habitational name from Béville (Moselle) or Béville-le-Comte (Eure-et-Loir), or a variant of <b>Beuville</b>, a habitational name from Beuville (Calvados). The surname <i>Béville</i> is rare in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Bevill","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Beville  ."]},{"name":"Bovill","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of several places in Normandy whose medieval forms share a similar range of variants, such as Bouville (Seine-Maritime), any of several places called Biéville (Calvados, Manche) or Biville (Manche, Seine-Maritime), Beuzeville-la-Giffard (Seine-Maritime), Boiville (Orne), and perhaps Boudeville (Seine-Maritime). See also   Boswell   and   Beville  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Beville was born in 1039, in Normandy, France. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1086, in Upton, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1039–after 1086":"1039–pärast 1086","1086–1125":"1086–1125","1039–1086":"1039–1086","1039":"1039","1125":"1125","after 1086":"pärast 1086","1086":"1086","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Upton, Huntingdonshire, England":"Upton, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1039–after 1086":"1039–1086 jälkeen","1086–1125":"1086–1125","1039–1086":"1039–1086","1039":"1039","1125":"1125","after 1086":"1086 jälkeen","1086":"1086","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska","Upton, Huntingdonshire, England":"Upton, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1039–after 1086":"1039–après 1086","1086–1125":"1086–1125","1039–1086":"1039–1086","1039":"1039","1125":"1125","after 1086":"après 1086","1086":"1086","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","Upton, Huntingdonshire, England":"Upton, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William de Beville est né en 1039, à Normandie, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé après 1086, à Upton, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1039–after 1086":"1039–nach 1086","1086–1125":"1086–1125","1039–1086":"1039–1086","1039":"1039","1125":"1125","after 1086":"nach 1086","1086":"1086","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankreich","Upton, Huntingdonshire, England":"Upton, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"William de Beville wurde 1039 in Normandie, Frankreich geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb nach 1086 in Upton, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1039–after 1086":"1039–after 1086","1086–1125":"1086–1125","1039–1086":"1039–1086","1039":"1039","1125":"1125","after 1086":"after 1086","1086":"1086","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","Upton, Huntingdonshire, England":"Upton, Cambridgeshire, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1039–after 1086":"1039–1086 után","1086–1125":"1086–1125","1039–1086":"1039–1086","1039":"1039","1125":"